<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="530" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d530">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/2902</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-13">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 13, 1915</hi>.</date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1920. Foreign Office informs me that American steamship <hi rend="italic">Ogeechee</hi> has arrived at Stornoway with cargo
                                loaded entirely at Bremen which port she left April 3, and that
                                under terms of order in council of March 11, vessel has been ordered
                                to proceed to Sharpness to discharge cargo, after which she will be
                                permitted to proceed to her destination.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>